@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title A Later Read Can Return an Older Value

actor Writer
actor Alice
actor Bob

participant athens
participant byzantium
participant cyrene

' [step1 {"name":"All Replicas Start at x=0"}]
note over athens
"order:1001" = "x=0", time=1
end note
/ note over byzantium
"order:1001" = "x=0", time=1
end note
/ note over cyrene
"order:1001" = "x=0", time=1
end note
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"New Write Is Delayed", "newPage":"true"}]
Writer -> athens : set "order:1001", "x=1"
athens -> athens : store "x=1", time=2
athens -[#red]> byzantium : replicate "x=1", time=2\n(delayed)
athens -[#red]> cyrene : replicate "x=1", time=2\n(delayed)

note over athens
"order:1001" = "x=1", time=2
end note

note over byzantium,cyrene
Replication is still in flight,
so both replicas still store "x=0".
end note
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Alice Sees the New Value", "newPage":"true"}]
Alice -> athens : get "order:1001"
athens -> byzantium : get "order:1001"
athens <-- byzantium : "x=0", time=1

note over athens
Read quorum includes one fresh replica,
so the coordinator returns
"x=1", time=2.
end note

athens --> Alice : "x=1"
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"A Different Quorum Is Still Old", "newPage":"true"}]
note over byzantium,athens #FFEEEE
Temporary partition:
byzantium cannot reach athens.
end note

note over byzantium,cyrene
These two replicas still hold
"order:1001" = "x=0", time=1.
end note
' [/step4]

' [step5 {"name":"Bob Later Sees the Old Value", "newPage":"true"}]
Bob -> byzantium : get "order:1001"
byzantium -[#red]>x athens : get "order:1001"
byzantium -> cyrene : get "order:1001"
byzantium <-- cyrene : "x=0", time=1

note over byzantium
This quorum only sees old data,
so it returns "x=0".
end note

byzantium --> Bob : "x=0"
' [/step5]

' [step6 {"name":"Replicas Eventually Converge", "newPage":"true"}]
athens --> byzantium : delayed "x=1", time=2 arrives
athens --> cyrene : delayed "x=1", time=2 arrives

note over athens #E6FFE6
"order:1001" = "x=1", time=2
end note
/ note over byzantium
"order:1001" = "x=1", time=2
end note
/ note over cyrene
"order:1001" = "x=1", time=2
end note

note bottom #FFE6E6
**Quorum Anomaly**
Alice saw "x=1", but Bob later saw "x=0".
The system eventually converges, but the
client-visible history is not linearizable.
end note
' [/step6]

@enduml
